---
description: PeopleCode code quality review — meta-SQL, .Value/record access, declared variables, SQL safety, error handling
alwaysApply: false
---

Use this rule when the user asks you to review PeopleCode for **code quality** — hardcoded table/date literals vs. meta-SQL (`%Table`, `%DateIn`, `%List`), unsafe `.Value`/rowset-record-field access chains, `Local`/`Component`/`Global` variable scope and naming, SQL string concatenation vs. bind variables, error handling, duplication, and event-placement discipline.

Full instructions: [AGENT.md](./AGENT.md).

For effective-date, join, key, or data-source *correctness* bugs (not quality/style), use the sibling rule in `../review-data-correctness/cursor.mdc` instead — apply both when reviewing a full program.

This rule is **not** about the Morris PeopleSoft Utilities Chrome extension's own TypeScript source — do not apply it to `src/` code review.
